<div class="courseblock main">
<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>TAPS 10200.  Acting Fundamentals.  100 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
This course introduces fundamental concepts of performance in the theater with emphasis on the development of creative faculties and techniques of observation, as well as vocal and physical interpretation. Concepts are introduced through directed reading, improvisation, and scene study.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
Instructor(s): L. Buxbaum, C. Cooper, G. Pasculli, D. de Mayo, H. Coleman, P. Pascoe     Terms Offered: Autumn
Spring
Summer
Winter<br/>
